## US-001 Fix: PDF Parser Unicode Character Matching

Based on my analysis of the logs, here's the fix required for `src/lib/pdf-parser.ts`:

### Changes Required:

Replace Chinese characters with Unicode escape sequences in regex patterns:

| Character | Unicode Escape | Purpose |
|-----------|----------------|---------|
| `节` | `\u8282` | Session/period marker (X-Y 节 format) |
| `☆` | `\u2606` | Star marker for course names |
| `周` | `\u5468` | Week marker (第 X 周 format) |

### Example Fix:

**Before (problematic):**
```typescript
const sessionMatch = text.match(/(\d+)-(\d+) 节/);
const courseMatch = text.match(/(.+?)☆/);
const weekMatch = text.match(/第 ([\u4e00-\u9fa5]+) 周/);
```

**After (fixed):**
```typescript
const sessionMatch = text.match(/(\d+)-(\d+)\u8282/);
const courseMatch = text.match(/(.+?)\u2606/);
const weekMatch = text.match(/第 ([\u4e00-\u9fa5]+)\u5468/);
```

